# draft repo: layout and tooling

- **Tracked repos** are in **`sources.yaml`** at **`~/.draft/sources.yaml`** (or **`$DRAFT_HOME/sources.yaml`**; default **DRAFT_HOME** is **~/.draft**). Repo ships **`sources.example.yaml`**; setup/app create `sources.yaml` in DRAFT_HOME when missing. Each key = subdirectory name; each value has `source` (path or GitHub URL) and optional `url` (git origin). At most one `url` per repo; duplicates normalized on pull. For local git repos, `url` is added when using `pull.py -a` or on the next pull. Pulled docs and vault live under **`~/.draft/`** (or **`DRAFT_HOME`**): `~/.draft/.doc_sources/<name>/` and `~/.draft/vault/`.
- **Sources:** `source` can be a **local path** (e.g. `../OtherRepo`, `./MarginCall`) or a **GitHub URL** (e.g. `https://github.com/owner/repo`). GitHub sources are fetched via the API (no clone); same `.md` exclusions as local.
- **Pull is pull-only:** `scripts/pull.py` copies from source into `~/.draft/.doc_sources/<name>/` when newer; it does **not** delete files when they are removed from the source.
- **Setup:** `./setup.sh` creates `.venv`, installs deps, and installs the activation banner (figlet-style “Draft”, PWD, tracked repos).

# Document UI (ui/)

- **Run:** `python scripts/serve.py` or `uvicorn ui.app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8058` from repo root; open http://localhost:8058.
- **Features:** Document tree, markdown viewer, Pull button, Add source box (GitHub URL or local path), full-text search (Whoosh), pin repos to top, system console.
- **Search:** Index under `.search_index/`; rebuilt after each Pull. `GET /api/search?q=...`; `POST /api/reindex` to rebuild manually.
- **APIs:** `GET /api/tree`, `GET /api/doc/{repo}/{path}`, `GET /api/search?q=...`, `POST /api/pull`, `POST /api/add_source`, `POST /api/reindex`.

# Adding a new repo

**Preferred:** From draft root run `python3 scripts/pull.py -a REPO` where REPO is: **repo name** (e.g. `OtherRepo` → `../OtherRepo`), **path** (e.g. `../OtherRepo`, `./path/to/repo`), or **GitHub URL** (e.g. `https://github.com/owner/repo` → fetch via API; subdir `owner_repo`). Script updates `sources.yaml`, adds `url` for local git repos, runs pull.

**From UI:** Use the Add source box in the sidebar; enter GitHub URL or local path. Pull runs after add.

**Manual:** Add an entry to `sources.yaml` under `repos` (name → `source` path or URL; `url` optional, backfilled for local git). Then run `python3 scripts/pull.py` or copy `.md` files manually with the same structure and exclusions.

# .md rules and exclusions

- Copy only **`.md`** files; preserve directory structure (e.g. `docs/foo.md` → `~/.draft/.doc_sources/<RepoName>/docs/foo.md`).
- Create only directories that contain at least one copied `.md`.
- **Exclude:** top-level `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/`, `.cursor/`, `.vscode/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `.venv/`, `.git/`, `__pycache__/`, `.tmp/`, `.adk/`.

# scripts/pull.py options

- **Default:** Pull from all repos in `sources.yaml` (copy when source newer; GitHub sources via API).
- **`-v`** — Verbose: repo name, tree of tracked files (like `tree`), then status line.
- **`-r DIRECTORY`** — List included `.md` files from a repo in tree format (any path).
- **`-s`** — With `-r`, show first 3 lines of each file.
- **`-a REPO`** — Add repo (name, path, or GitHub URL), update `sources.yaml`, add `url` if local git repo, run pull.

To stop tracking: remove the repo from `sources.yaml` and optionally delete its subdirectory under `~/.draft/.doc_sources/<name>`.
